						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Stone fixed into a wall of the Dēyavva temple.</hi></p>						

						<p>A.D. 1699.</p>						

						<p>This record is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1621, Pramāthi, Dakshiṇāyana, Bhādrapada, Paurṇami. Wednesday, Pūrvā-Bhādrapada-nakshatra,</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">1699 A.D., August 30.</hi> There was, however, no <hi rend="italic">Saṁkrānti</hi> on that day.</p>						

						<p>The inscription, in Sanskrit language and Nāgari characters, states that a well was constructed by Rāya-Paṇḍita, son of Rāmachandra who was the son of Tīrthēs11a.</p>						

						</summary>
